(43, 13, 32, 58, 1, 2, 3, 'God shall also glorify him', 'Glorification of the Son', 'This connection highlights the theme of glorification present in both passages. John 13:32 speaks of God glorifying the Son, while Hebrews 1:3 describes the Son as the brightness of God''s glory, emphasizing His exalted status.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 32, 60, 3, 22, 22, 'God shall also glorify him', 'Glorification and Authority Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of glorification and authority. In John 13:32, the glorification of Jesus by God is emphasized, while 1 Peter 3:22 speaks of Jesus'' exaltation and authority at God''s right hand.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 32, 66, 3, 21, 21, 'God shall also glorify him', 'Glorification and Overcoming', 'This connection highlights the theme of glorification in both passages. John 13:32 speaks of God glorifying Jesus, while Revelation 3:21 promises that those who overcome will share in His throne, reflecting a shared glory.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 33, 43, 7, 33, 34, NULL, 'Connection of Jesus'' Departure', 'Both passages emphasize the temporary presence of Jesus and the impending separation from His followers. The phrases about seeking Him and not being able to follow highlight a shared theme of longing and limitation in understanding His mission.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
