(43, 13, 33, 62, 2, 1, 1, 'little children', 'Connection of Guidance and Advocacy', 'This connection highlights the theme of Jesus'' care for His followers. In John 13:33, He addresses them as ''little children,'' while 1 John 2:1 continues this address, emphasizing the need for guidance and the assurance of an advocate in Jesus Christ.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 33, 48, 4, 19, 19, 'little children', 'Connection of Spiritual Parenthood', 'This connection highlights the theme of spiritual nurturing, as both passages address the speaker''s relationship with ''little children.'' John 13:33 speaks to the disciples'' need for guidance, while Galatians 4:19 expresses a desire for Christ''s formation in believers.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 33, 62, 4, 4, 4, 'little children', 'Connection of Overcoming and Guidance', 'This connection highlights the theme of guidance and strength. In John 13:33, Jesus speaks to ''little children'' about His impending departure, while 1 John 4:4 reassures them of their strength in overcoming challenges through God.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 34, 49, 5, 2, 2, 'love one another', 'Love as Central Command', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of love, with John 13:34 presenting love as a commandment and Ephesians 5:2 urging believers to walk in love. The connection highlights the importance of Christ''s love as a model for how believers should love one another.', 'theme', 0.8739999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 34, 3, 19, 18, 18, 'love one another', 'Love Commandment Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of love, with John 13:34 presenting a new commandment to love one another as Jesus loved, while Leviticus 19:18 instructs to love one''s neighbor as oneself. This connection highlights the continuity of the theme of love in both the Old and New Testaments.', 'theme', 0.776, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 34, 43, 15, 17, 17, 'love one another', 'Command to Love One Another', 'Both passages emphasize the command to love one another, highlighting its importance in the teachings of Jesus. The repetition of this command reinforces the centrality of love in the community of believers.', 'theme', 0.7689999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 34, 60, 1, 22, 22, 'love one another', 'Love One Another Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the command to love one another, highlighting the importance of love in the Christian community. John 13:34 introduces this commandment, while 1 Peter 1:22 reinforces it by urging love with a pure heart.', 'theme', 0.713, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 34, 48, 6, 2, 2, 'love one another', 'Love and Burden Bearing', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of loving one another. John 13:34''s command to love is fulfilled in Galatians 6:2 through the act of bearing each other''s burdens.', 'theme', 0.622, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 34, 46, 12, 26, 27, 'love one another', 'Love and Unity in Community', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of love and unity among believers. John 13:34''s command to ''love one another'' resonates with 1 Corinthians 12:26-27''s depiction of the body of Christ, where members share in each other''s experiences, highlighting interconnectedness.', 'theme', 0.601, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 34, 62, 3, 23, 23, 'love one another', 'Connection of Love Commandments', 'Both passages emphasize the commandment to love one another, linking the teachings of Jesus with the apostolic instruction. This connection highlights the continuity of love as a central tenet in Christian teaching.', 'theme', 0.601, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 35, 62, 4, 20, 21, 'love one to another', 'Love as a Mark of Discipleship', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of love among believers. John 13:35 states that love identifies Jesus'' disciples, while 1 John 4:20-21 asserts that love for one''s brother is essential to loving God.', 'theme', 0.6779999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 35, 62, 2, 10, 10, 'love one to another', 'Love as a Discipleship Marker', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of love among believers. John 13:35 states that love identifies disciples, while 1 John 2:10 highlights that loving one''s brother signifies living in the light.', 'theme', 0.517, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 35, 43, 17, 21, 21, 'love one to another', 'Unity Through Love', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of unity among believers. John 13:35 highlights love as a defining characteristic of discipleship, while John 17:21 expresses the desire for believers to be one, reflecting the unity of the Father and the Son.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 13, 35, 44, 4, 32, 35, 'love one to another', 'Love and Community in Action', 'This connection highlights the theme of love among believers as expressed in John 13:35, where love is a defining characteristic of discipleship. Acts 4:32-35 illustrates this love through the communal sharing of possessions, demonstrating that true discipleship involves caring for one another''s needs.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
